SIMPLE: spanking
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: spanking
<hw>spank"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Moving with a quick,
lively pace, or capable of so doing; dashing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Four <qex>spanking</qex> grays ready harnessed.</q> <rj><qau>G.
Colman, the Younger.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Large; considerable.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Very; extremely; -- used especially in the phrase
<ecol><b>spanking new</b></ecol> or <ecol><b>brand spanking
new</b></ecol>, meaning completely new and unused.</def>
<mark>[informal]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>spanking breeze</ent>⟦br⟧
